review_blob: Pours amber colored with small white head. Small lacing on the glass. Floral and citrus aroma. Taste is very hoppy, slighty bitter, goes down smooth with a musky aftertaste. Overall a very good IPA
Very smooth belgian ale. low butterness with full flavor. blah blah blah i have nothing to add
ok beer for casual drinking. hops come out but the aftertaste does not deliver. ok for drinking games
Not a very elite brew. Low taste, very bland. Honestly this would be a good drinking game beer
Pours dark amber, aroma is weak citrus, taste is good bitter and strong citrus. Taste fades quickly. Overall a good average level ipa
One of the best ipa i have ever had. Amazing aroma of hops with floral notes. Nice head with proper lacing. Taste is consitant and just bitter enough.
Beer has dark red appearance with ivory head. Nice lacing down the glass. Initial taste is sharp however the cherry comes out almost immediately. Finishes mellow flavor lingers nicely.
Golden clear color with thick white head. Laces nicely down bottle. Faint bitter smell with citrus and floral notes. Initial bitterness melts away smoothly with consistant flavor
Nice creamy head laces down the glass. Dark golden color very hoppy citrus aroma. First taste features an abundance of hops with a clean finish. No bad aftertaste. Mild bitterness lingers well.
